{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880161797,"sessionID":"ses_2854c1212ffe5mg15gx9q7QRtB","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab4c6490017vg7TisGJ47giI","messageID":"msg_d7ab4bdd1001Yayf4P6RKJ6Igw","sessionID":"ses_2854c1212ffe5mg15gx9q7QRtB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7c9e7dfcebcd4ea9894a3c3d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/example/pcap-analyzer/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/example/pcap-analyzer/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PCAP Analyzer\n2: \n3: Network traffic analysis service using AgentCube Code Interpreter and LLM orchestration.\n4: \n5: ## Overview\n6: \n7: The PCAP Analyzer is a FastAPI application that provides an API for analyzing network capture (PCAP) files using AI-powered agents. It leverages AgentCube's Code Interpreter to execute Python code for network traffic analysis.\n8: \n9: ## Architecture\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐\n13: │   Client    │────▶│  FastAPI    │────▶│  LLM Orchestrator│\n14: └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └──────────────────┘\n15:                                                 │\n16:                    ┌────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┐\n17:                    │                            │                            │\n18:                    ▼                            ▼                            ▼\n19:             ┌─────────────┐             ┌─────────────┐            ┌─────────────┐\n20:             │  Planner    │             │   ReAct     │            │  Reporter  │\n21:             │   Agent     │             │    Agent    │            │   Agent    │\n22:             └─────────────┘             └─────────────┘            └─────────────┘\n23:                    │                            │                            │\n24:                    └────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┘\n25:                                                 │\n26:                                      ┌──────────┴──────────┐\n27:                                      │ AgentCube Sandbox   │\n28:                                      │ (Code Interpreter)  │\n29:                                      └─────────────────────┘\n30: ```\n31: \n32: ## Features\n33: \n34: - **LLM-Powered Analysis**: Uses large language models to generate analysis scripts\n35: - **ReAct Agent**: Implements Reasoning + Acting pattern for interactive analysis\n36: - **Sandbox Execution**: Runs Python code securely in AgentCube sandboxes\n37: - **REST API**: Simple HTTP API for submitting PCAP files and getting analysis results\n38: \n39: ## Prerequisites\n40: \n41: - Python 3.12+\n42: - OpenAI-compatible API key\n43: - Access to AgentCube services (Router and Workload Manager)\n44: \n45: ## Installation\n46: \n47: ### Local Development\n48: \n49: ```bash\n50: # Clone the repository\n51: cd example/pcap-analyzer\n52: \n53: # Create virtual environment\n54: python -m venv .venv\n55: source .venv/bin/activate\n56: \n57: # Install dependencies\n58: pip install -r requirements.txt\n59: \n60: # Set environment variables\n61: export OPENAI_API_KEY=your-api-key\n62: export ROUTER_URL=http://localhost:8080\n63: export WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://localhost:8080\n64: \n65: # Run the server\n66: python pcap_analyzer.py\n67: ```\n68: \n69: ### Docker\n70: \n71: ```bash\n72: # Build the image\n73: docker build -t pcap-analyzer:latest .\n74: \n75: # Run the container\n76: docker run -p 8000:8000 \\\n77:   -e OPENAI_API_KEY=your-api-key \\\n78:   -e ROUTER_URL=http://router:8080 \\\n79:   -e WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://workload-manager:8080 \\\n80:   pcap-analyzer:latest\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ### Kubernetes\n84: \n85: ```bash\n86: # Update the secret with your API key\n87: kubectl create secret generic pcap-analyzer-secrets \\\n88:   --from-literal=openai-api-key=your-api-key\n89: \n90: # Apply the deployment\n91: kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ## Configuration\n95: \n96: The following environment variables can be configured:\n97: \n98: | Variable | Default | Description |\n99: |----------|---------|-------------|\n100: | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | (required) | OpenAI-compatible API key |\n101: | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` | API endpoint |\n102: | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` | Model name |\n103: | `ROUTER_URL` | (required) | AgentCube Router URL |\n104: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | (required) | AgentCube Workload Manager URL |\n105: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | `my-interpreter` | Code interpreter name |\n106: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | `default` | Kubernetes namespace |\n107: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | `5` | Sandbox warmup duration |\n108: \n109: ## API Endpoints\n110: \n111: ### POST /analyze\n112: \n113: Analyze a PCAP file.\n114: \n115: **Request:**\n116: \n117: ```bash\n118: # With file upload\n119: curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/analyze \\\n120:   -F \"pcap_file=@capture.pcap\" \\\n121:   -F \"question=What are the top talkers in this network?\"\n122: \n123: # With file path\n124: curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/analyze \\\n125:   -F \"pcap_path=/data/capture.pcap\" \\\n126:   -F \"question=List all HTTP requests\"\n127: ```\n128: \n129: **Response:**\n130: \n131: ```json\n132: {\n133:   \"script\": \"from scapy.all import *\\n...\",\n134:   \"results\": \"10.0.0.1: 1234 packets\\n10.0.0.2: 567 packets\",\n135:   \"report\": \"## Analysis Report\\n\\n...\"\n136: }\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### GET /health\n140: \n141: Health check endpoint.\n142: \n143: **Response:**\n144: \n145: ```json\n146: {\n147:   \"status\": \"healthy\"\n148: }\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ## Components\n152: \n153: ### SandboxRunner\n154: \n155: Manages the AgentCube sandbox session, including:\n156: - Starting and stopping sessions\n157: - Uploading files\n158: - Executing commands\n159: \n160: ### Planner Agent\n161: \n162: Generates Python scripts for PCAP analysis based on the user's question.\n163: \n164: ### ReAct Agent\n165: \n166: Implements the Reasoning + Acting pattern for iterative analysis.\n167: \n168: ### Reporter Agent\n169: \n170: Generates human-readable reports from analysis results.\n171: \n172: ## Example Questions\n173: \n174: - \"What are the top 10 source IP addresses by packet count?\"\n175: - \"List all HTTP requests and their response codes\"\n176: - \"What protocols are used in this capture?\"\n177: - \"Show DNS queries and their responses\"\n178: - \"Find all TCP connections\"\n179: \n180: ## Troubleshooting\n181: \n182: ### OPENAI_API_KEY not set\n183: \n184: ```\n185: ERROR: OPENAI_API_KEY environment variable is not set\n186: ```\n187: \n188: Set the environment variable before starting the service.\n189: \n190: ### Connection refused to Router/Workload Manager\n191: \n192: Ensure AgentCube services are running and accessible from the analyzer.\n193: \n194: ### Analysis timeout\n195: \n196: Increase the timeout or simplify the analysis question.\n197: \n198: ## License\n199: \n200: Apache 2.0\n\n(End of file - total 200 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PCAP Analyzer\n\nNetwork traffic analysis service using AgentCube Code Interpreter and LLM orchestration.\n\n## Overview\n\nThe PCAP Analyzer is a FastAPI application that provides an API for analyzing network capture (PCAP) files using AI-powered agents. It leverages AgentCube's Code Interpreter to execute Python code for network traffic analysis.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐\n│   Client    │────▶│  FastAPI    │────▶│  LLM Orchestrator│\n└─────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └──────────────────┘\n                                                │\n                   ┌────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┐\n                   │                            │                            │\n                   ▼                            ▼                            ▼\n            ┌─────────────┐             ┌─────────────┐            ┌─────────────┐\n            │  Planner    │             │   ReAct     │            │  Reporter  │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/example/pcap-analyzer/README.md","time":{"start":1775880161790,"end":1775880161795}}}}
