{"type":"text","timestamp":1775880575979,"sessionID":"ses_2854c1212ffe5mg15gx9q7QRtB","part":{"id":"prt_d7abb0580001u4KYJyGMwCtCyi","messageID":"msg_d7abaea4d001wBESkmCNuuL6lA","sessionID":"ses_2854c1212ffe5mg15gx9q7QRtB","type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Let me provide a summary of the implementation:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've implemented the AR-037 PCAP analyzer example application with the following changes:\n\n### 1. SandboxRunner Context Manager Support\nAdded `__enter__` and `__exit__` methods to the `SandboxRunner` class in `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py:98-105`\n\n### 2. Added scapy to requirements.txt\nAdded `scapy>=2.5.0` to `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`\n\n### 3. Package Structure Fixes\n- Created `example/__init__.py` and `example/pcap-analyzer/__init__.py` to make them proper Python packages\n- Created symlink `example/pcap_analyzer` -> `example/pcap-analyzer` for Python import compatibility\n\n### 4. Test Infrastructure Fixes\n- Fixed `tests/conftest.py` to properly reset environment variables between tests\n- Added test for context manager support in `tests/test_pcap_analyzer.py`\n- Fixed `test_sandbox_runner_initialization` to clear sys.modules before importing\n\n### Test Results\nAll 15 tests pass:\n- Configuration tests (default values, env var overrides)\n- SandboxRunner tests (initialization, custom parameters, start requirements, stop, context manager)\n- AnalyzeResponse tests\n- FastAPI app tests (root, health)\n- Planner and Reporter agent tests","time":{"start":1775880575977,"end":1775880575977}}}
